Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteSizeBlockage(25.10)                            deleteSizeBlockage(25.10)

Name
       deleteSizeBlockage - Deletes a size blockage object

Syntax
        deleteSizeBlockage

       [-help]

       [-name <blockageName>]

       [-selected]

       [-all]

       Deletes a size blockage object. You can use this command after resizing
       the floorplan.

Parameters
       -all   Deletes all the size blockages.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each deleteSizeBlockage parameter. For a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man deleteSizeBlockage

       -name <blockageName>
              Specifies the name of the size blockage that is to be deleted.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -selected
              Deletes the selected size blockage.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command creates a size blockage and deletes it:

                addSizeBlockage -name sizeBlkg1 -box 400 400 500 500

                deleteSizeBlockage -name sizeBlkg1

Related Information
